  File <span class="token string">"&lt;stdin>"</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> line <span class="token number">1</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token keyword">in</span> <span class="token operator">&lt;</span>module<span class="token operator">></span>
ModuleNotFoundError<span class="token punctuation">:</span> No module named <span class="token string">'maths'</span>
<span class="token operator">>></span><span class="token operator">></span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true"><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><p>In the example above, I added an extra s to math deliberately and <em>ModuleNotFoundError</em> was raised. Lets fix it by removing the extra s from math.</p>
